  <span id="freeText12540188531497828874" style="display:none">I grew up spending my free time in my fathers lab and later I was married to a scientist. We celebrated together with deep appreciation and wonder when he purchased his first mass spectrometer. Our children grew up wandering about his lab, helping out during summer time breaks. We have a tremendous love and appreciation of the outdoors, camping, travelling, hiking, collecting.<br /><br />Ah, I thought, here is the perfect book for me to read!<br /><br />Though I consider myself to be a broad minded intellect I can't understand what people see in this monotonous bio. I hung in there page after page, chapter after chapter hoping it would get better. It never did. </span>
